What you need to know:

Jihadists have seized swathes of territory in Borno, Boko Haram's birthplace, forcing some two million to flee their homes.Most of the displaced have moved into squalid camps in the regional capital, Maiduguri, relying on food handouts from international charities.Since 2018, people have returned to five major towns where they typically live behind a defensive line of trenches to fend off jihadists.